messages.content: The Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT) is located in Cambridge, Massachusetts [collegeadvisor](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1) [campus360](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2). The specific address is 77 Massachusetts Avenue, Cambridge, MA 02139 [collegeadvisor](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0) [studypoint](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-3) [mit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4) [collegeboard](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-5) [diacomp](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-6) [campus360](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-2]. The campus is situated across the Charles River from Boston [collegeadvisor](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0), occupying a 168-acre (68 ha) area that extends approximately one mile (1.6 km) along the Cambridge side of the Charles River basin [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-7) [topuniversities](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8) [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). MIT's campus merges with Cambridge neighborhoods, including Kendall Square [topuniversities](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-8], and is located between Central and Kendall Squares [collegeadvisor](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). The Kendall/MIT MBTA Red Line station is on the northeastern edge of the campus, in Kendall Square [wikipedia](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-1). The Welcome Center is located at 292 Main Street, Cambridge, MA 02142 [collegeadvisor](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-0). A campus map is available online [mit](https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/id/0-4).
